### Module Lifecycle

Shared code follows a maturity lifecycle:

1. **Prototype** in a workstream directory — quick and dirty, owned by one agent
2. **Stabilise** in `lib/` — extract when useful to multiple workstreams, add tests
3. **Graduate** to a shared package — when the module is mature and needed across repos

### Scope Tags

Use `scope` in YAML frontmatter so agents can discover relevant docs:

```yaml
scope: [feature-name]               # single workstream
scope: [feature-a, feature-b]       # cross-cutting
scope: [all]                        # foundational/shared
```

Agents can discover relevant docs with: `grep -r "scope:.*feature-name" docs/`

Or use the doc index: `python tools/doc-index.py --scope feature-name`

## Documentation Rules

- **One topic per file** — keep docs focused and scannable
- **Clear filenames** — descriptive kebab-case, no ambiguous abbreviations
- **Frontmatter required** — every doc needs `title`, `scope`, `updated` (or `created`)
- **Reasonable size** — if a doc exceeds ~200 lines, split into focused sub-docs
- **Architecture docs** include decision rationale inline (no separate decisions/ directory)

### Doc Directory Types

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `architecture/` | How the system works and why (decisions included) |
| `reference/` | Knowledge base: domain, techniques, foundations |
| `guides/` | How to do things (setup, running tools, workflows) |
| `guides/tools/` | Index of all tools with links to co-located docs |
| `plans/` | Forward-looking ideas and roadmaps |

### Tool Documentation Convention

Tool docs live with the code, not in `docs/guides/`:

- Hub tools (`lib/web_*.py`) → `lib/docs/{tool-name}.md`
- Pipelines → `pipelines/{name}/docs/README.md`
- Standalone scripts (`tools/`) → `docs/guides/{guide-name}.md` (workflow-oriented)
- `docs/guides/tools/README.md` is the master index pointing to all of the above

## Doc Index

Build and query the documentation index:

```bash
# Build static index from frontmatter
python tools/doc-index.py --build

# Query by scope, tag, or status
python tools/doc-index.py --scope feature-name --tag keyword

# JSON output for piping
python tools/doc-index.py --scope all --json

# Build + query in one step
python tools/doc-index.py --build --scope feature-name --status completed
```

The index is written to `.doc-index.json` — one Read call gets all doc metadata.
